  <div class="spacer"></div>
  <div class="article">#1
    <p class="title" onclick="toggle('1')">
      Resize disk in gnome boxes
    </p>
    <p class="age">
      10/03/2018
    </p>
    <p id="1" class="abody">
      Right-click on a VM, open the properties and there you can resize the disk. However, at least Windows, will show a disk size equal to 20GB by default and even if you
      change the disk size nothing seems to happen. You need to use the partition tool of Windows to resize the disk, in fact there will be an empty space unused.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="article">#2
    <p class="title" onclick="toggle('2')">
      Share files and folders with virtual machines (e.g. gnome-boxes)
    </p>
    <p class="age">
      10/03/2018
    </p>
    <p id="2" class="abody">
      Some virtual machines doesn't provide a way to share folders. In general you need to install some add-ons. An easy solution is to use a mini-ftp server. You can use
      python on the host machine running <span class="cmd">python -m pyftpdlib -w</span> inside the shared folder (-w is for the writing permission). Then, you can easily access that folder from the guest
      machine with a ftp client or directly with the file explorer.
    </p>
  </div>
  <script>
    //if there is an id in the url, show the related article
    var url = window.location.href;
    var res = url.split("#");
    if (res.length == 2) { //there is an id
      toggle(res[1]);
    }
  </script>
